As you are using react-navigation using createStackNavigator you could add the backHandler control only inside your `initialRouteName` screen, but you&#39;ll need to add an eventListener to check if the screen you are watching is actually the one that&#39;s focused, else it would trigger also in your other screens

If this is not the case, to check the length of your stack, inside your screen you can simply check it using your navigation prop:

    handleBackPress=()=&gt;{
