When you put

    this.Controls()

you get `Control`s which are explicitly on `this` (form) *only*. It seems that `TextBox`es you want to clear are placed in *containers* 
(`Panel`s, `Groupbox`es etc.) so you should enumerate them:

    private static IEnumerable&lt;T&gt; AllControls&lt;T&gt;(Control parent) 
      where T : Control {

      if (null == parent)
        yield break;

      if (parent is T control)
        yield return control;

      foreach (Control item in parent.Controls)
        foreach (T ctrl in AllControls&lt;T&gt;(item))
          yield return ctrl;
    }

Then it&#39;s easy to clear them:

    foreach(TextBox textBox in AllControls&lt;TextBox&gt;(this))
      textBox.Text = &quot;&quot;;

